<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>take a long look • take a long view</xh5><p> <i>take a long look</i>—(also: take a long, hard look) make a detailed and intense examination: Wisconsin residents should <u>take a long look</u> at what their so-called representatives are doing with their money.</p><p> <i>take a long view—</i>consider events, etc. a long time ahead; have regard for the future: Kennedy called for Americans to <u>take a long view</u> when analyzing their current situation.</p> </entry>
